Subject: [PATCH 04/87] std.posix: panic on unexpected error in `munmap`
X-Developer-Signature: v=1; a=openpgp-sha256; l=1173; i=xtexchooser@duck.com;
 h=from:subject; bh=KDPCdDS4LGjFANiEzDlNe+IM2IpT7XOov1a/e10JSs0=;
 b=owGbwMvMwCW2U4Ij7wZL9ETG02pJDJkmdhaPdX+kHT91hStj5e4LJgriUgx2cQFvHD2bX9XKz
 a0R1xPvKGVhEONikBVTZCkybPBm1UnnF11WLgszh5UJZAgDF6cATOTSGYa/Qpf22Iv7aGRfZUqp
 jd82J2jPo6z1B6+n/VWcvrzzofq0I4wM/+6KdG86rRRsk/g9+f5zl/roGp+TwqIff3/bu9bZd3U
 KKwA=
X-Developer-Key: i=xtexchooser@duck.com; a=openpgp;
 fpr=7231804B052C670F15A6771DB918086ED8045B91

This is to help diagnose #25498. We can't use `unexpectedErrno` here,
because `std.posix.munmap` is infallible. So, when the flag is set to
report unexpected errnos, we just call `std.debug.panic` to provide
details instead of doing `unreachable`.

Pushing straight to master after running checks locally; there's no
point waiting for CI on the PR just for this.

(cherry picked from commit 923ddd94a1419abfa9ab95718a7b7d2a8da7a5ec)
---
 lib/std/posix.zig | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/lib/std/posix.zig b/lib/std/posix.zig
index 85b0b331a092..3c7d52f773a5 100644
--- a/lib/std/posix.zig
+++ b/lib/std/posix.zig
@@ -4873,7 +4873,9 @@ pub fn munmap(memory: []align(page_size_min) const u8) void {
         .SUCCESS => return,
         .INVAL => unreachable, // Invalid parameters.
         .NOMEM => unreachable, // Attempted to unmap a region in the middle of an existing mapping.
-        else => unreachable,
+        else => |e| if (unexpected_error_tracing) {
+            std.debug.panic("unexpected errno: {d} ({t})", .{ @intFromEnum(e), e });
+        } else unreachable,
     }
 }
 
